’گگظقTitle: title: job unfreeze
Path: Examples
Content:
Unfreeze the latest frozen job.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> job unfreeze


```
Unfreeze a specific frozen job by its PID.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> job unfreeze 4


```
—ظTarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/job_unfreeze.mdظ@13918becaf6f314c2a6cb149897d28c1790f43121ecb117e01dc78ed13098cfa³title: job unfreeze‘¥Notesظ½When a running process is frozen (with the SIGTSTP signal or with the Ctrl-Z key on unix),

a background job gets registered for this process, which can then be resumed using this command.
’گگظيTitle: title: job unfreeze
Path: Notes
Content:
When a running process is frozen (with the SIGTSTP signal or with the Ctrl-Z key on unix),

a background job gets registered for this process, which can then be resumed using this command.
